posts.subject: This is what I love about the U.S.
posts.body:
It looks like folks have decided on “F-it” per lock-down. In L.A. a skate park that had been filled with sand was emptied by a hoard of kids with buckets, brooms, whatever. Police, who have an office about 200 yards away, decided not to try to arrest a mob of kids…

Taking assholes in stride - but at some point no longer putting up with them.


Too many of these "authorities" fail to realize they can be "retired" at any time. Only good nature prevents it.

Irreverence. Try some.

posts.subject: Morality Politics
posts.body:
It always seemed to me that the right was always arguing minutia over mathematical proofs - instead of communicating hard values. Honestly and clearly.

For instance:

We prefer freedom and a Bill of Rights.
We want our culture preserved.
And we don't believe we'll ever have the same degree of freedom within a "multicultural" society.

There's nothing wrong with those values or aspirations. So why do so many apologize for them? Where does this need to explain come from? Or the need to even excuse it?

There never was any need to vilify those who thought differently - only resolutely oppose them. "Not in our interests".

Blacks, deviants, social justice warriors, and communists deserve their own space to build their "shining example" for the world.

But they don't deserve even the slightest attention when telling us how WE wish to live.

It's very difficult to change minds. So, can we get off this treadmill? By respecting boundaries.

Spotted an article just this week. That CO baker is in trouble again for refusing to serve an alphabet. How is this possible?

What is the simplest signal one can send for "leave me alone"?

posts.subject: Springtime For Joggers
posts.body:
I really would like to know the truth here, but what I've seen smells. What would a Las Vegas bookie assign as the odds of this individual being innocent?


Not to put too fine a point on it, but generations of white people have had to pay the tax, the jogger tax, for sins they never committed and in fact, we never committed. Baltimore would go from Lagos on the Chesapeake to Hong Kong on the Chesapeake if the local joggers all decamped to another land. If not for the jogger phenomenon, alarm companies would go out of business and cars would have normal keys again. Everyone knows this. The jogger tax is the cost of being white.

posts.subject: What lies beneath
posts.body:
All of us have a stake in the truth here. Hope we learn it.


Maybe it is simply ideological fervor. We know from their private communications that most of these people were fanatics. Their Trump hatred was just one aspect of their zeal to serve the inner party.
Government will always be corrupt, as men are not angels. Whether it is the lust for power or the temptations that come with power, corruption is part of the human condition. A much more serious problem is a government overrun by fanatical ideologues. That may be the heart of this scandal. The long march through the institutions has been followed by a radicalization of the institutions. The inner party now operates like a religious cult, rather than a political operation.
